  "prompt": "I'm in love with my friend, but he loves someone else. What should I do to protect myself from being hurt, because I don't want to lose him, and I can't tell him?",
  "response": "Dealing with unrequited love can be challenging. Here are some suggestions to help you cope:\n\n1. Emotional self-care\n- Allow yourself to feel your emotions\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Consider talking to a therapist or counselor\n\n2. Create boundaries\n- Give yourself space from the situation\n- Limit time spent with him if needed\n- Focus on your own personal growth\n\n3. Distract and redirect\n- Pursue hobbies and interests\n- Spend time with other friends\n- Consider dating other people\n- Invest in personal development\n\n4. Acceptance strategies\n- Acknowledge your feelings without judgment\n- Understand that you can't control who someone loves\n- Recognize that your worth isn't defined by his feelings\n\n5. Preserve the friendship\n- Maintain respect for his feelings\n- Be supportive of his relationship\n- Don't create drama or tension\n- Stay authentic and kind\n\n6. Long-term perspective\n- Remember that feelings can change\n- Your emotional well-being is most important\n- You deserve someone who loves you completely\n\nIf the pain becomes overwhelming, speaking with a trusted friend or professional can provide additional support and guidance.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
